m)","¼ tsp fine sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","25 g milk","25 g butter"]}],"id":"r93516","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-S1kvgis9C_Q\/XZQxMpAqHtI\/AAAAAAAAcsw\/yqZ_LQZZHbU3VZpyA2C1B9PfNCEvifiUACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nu43acYKmLFrp31i.png","title":"Shepherd's Pie","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"20.6 g","fat":"18.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29.9 g","calories":"1547 kJ \/ 370 kcal"},"usefulItems":"rectangular baking dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm x 5 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["This dish can be made ahead then reheated for 35-40 minutes (190°C).","Another real British classic – and one most families have their own way of making! Here’s ours, which features leek in the potato topping. Traditionally a dish popular for using leftover roasted lamb, this winter warmer is a constant firm staple on British menus.","Works well served with steamed buttered cabbage."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 40m","6 portions"]}